---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Natural Immune System Support">
  <section class="page-intro intro-box">
    <h1>Natural Immune System Support</h1>
    <p>Your immune system is your body’s defense network — and like any system, it needs the right inputs and regular maintenance. Evidence supports four pillars: cleansing, liver support, antioxidants, and essential nutrients.</p>
  </section>

  <div class="grid">
    <!-- Cleansing -->
    <section class="card">
      <h2>Cleansing (Detoxification)</h2>
      <p>Cleansing supports your body’s elimination of metabolic waste and environmental toxins that can burden immune function.</p>
      <ul class="bullets">
        <li>May reduce inflammation burden and improve energy.</li>
        <li>Supports organs of elimination (liver, kidneys, gut, skin).</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="ref"><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6163475/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Research: Environmental toxins &amp; chronic disease (review)</a></p>
    </section>

    <!-- Liver Support -->
    <section class="card">
      <h2>Liver Support</h2>
      <p>The liver is the body’s primary detox organ, central to immune signaling and antigen clearance.</p>
      <ul class="bullets">
        <li>Processes xenobiotics, hormones, and inflammatory byproducts.</li>
        <li>Healthy liver function correlates with resilient immunity.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="ref"><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7144559/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Research: Liver–immune system interactions (review)</a></p>
    </section>

    <!-- Antioxidants -->
    <section class="card">
      <h2>Antioxidants</h2>
      <p>Antioxidants protect cells from oxidative stress and lipid peroxidation — processes linked to immune dysfunction and chronic disease.</p>
      <ul class="bullets">
        <li>Dietary antioxidants help neutralize excess free radicals.</li>
        <li>Associated with reduced risk of cardiometabolic and neurodegenerative disease.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="ref"><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3249911/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Research: Oxidative stress, antioxidants &amp; disease</a></p>
    </section>

    <!-- Essential Nutrients -->
    <section class="card">
      <h2>Essential Nutrients</h2>
      <p>Immune cells require steady supplies of vitamins, minerals, amino acids, and healthy fats. Even mild deficiencies can impair defenses.</p>
      <ul class="bullets">
        <li>Targeted nutrient testing can reveal hidden gaps.</li>
        <li>Correcting deficiencies improves immune competence.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="ref">
        <a href="https://ods.od.nih.gov/factsheets/VitaminC-Consumer/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">NIH: Vitamin C &amp; immunity</a> ·
        <a href="https://ods.od.nih.gov/factsheets/VitaminD-Consumer/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">NIH: Vitamin D</a> ·
        <a href="https://ods.od.nih.gov/factsheets/Zinc-Consumer/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">NIH: Zinc</a>
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>

  <section class="highlight-box">
    <h2>Root Cause Medicine</h2>
    <p>Root cause medicine starts with this premise: deficiencies and biochemical bottlenecks often drive disease states. Many people have <em>uptake</em> or <em>processing</em> variants (e.g., methylation, transporters) that limit how well they use certain vitamins and minerals — even with a good diet.</p>
    <ul class="bullets">
      <li><strong>Genetic &amp; functional testing:</strong> identify absorption/activation issues (e.g., B12, folate, vitamin D, zinc, iron).</li>
      <li><strong>Personalized repletion:</strong> fill the specific “holes” first; symptoms often persist until deficiencies are corrected.</li>
      <li><strong>Systems view:</strong> address triggers in gut, hormones, inflammation, sleep, stress, and environment.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="provider-callout">
      <p><strong>Featured Root-Cause Physician:</strong> <a href="https://DanPurserMD.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Dr. Dan Purser (DanPurserMD.com)</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="dual-care info-box">
    <h2>Functional &amp; Naturopathic Doctors — and Why We Suggest Both</h2>
    <p>We are not against medical doctors. The conventional medical system is designed to diagnose and treat symptoms — invaluable for acute care and serious diagnoses. We recommend <strong>both</strong>:</p>
    <ul class="bullets">
      <li><strong>Have an MD/DO:</strong> diagnostics, imaging, prescriptions, and acute care.</li>
      <li><strong>Add a functional or naturopathic doctor:</strong> deeper labs, lifestyle, and nutrient-first strategies to address root causes.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="finder grid-2">
      <div>
        <h3>What is a Functional Medicine Doctor?</h3>
        <p>MDs/DOs (and some NPs) trained to find upstream drivers of disease. They integrate advanced labs with nutrition, sleep, stress, toxin reduction, and targeted supplementation.</p>
        <p class="ref"><a href="https://www.ifm.org/functional-medicine/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Learn more (IFM)</a></p>
        <p><a class="btn" href="https://www.ifm.org/find-a-practitioner/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Find a Functional Medicine Practitioner</a></p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>What is a Naturopathic Doctor (ND)?</h3>
        <p>Clinicians trained in both conventional sciences and natural therapeutics (nutrition, botanicals, lifestyle). Focused on prevention and restoring function.</p>
        <p class="ref"><a href="https://aanmc.org/naturopathic-medicine/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Learn more (AANMC)</a></p>
        <p><a class="btn" href="https://naturopathic.org/page/FindAnND" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Find a Naturopathic Doctor</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="note">
      <p><strong>Second opinions save time.</strong> If you receive a diagnosis, consult your MD/DO <em>and</em> a root-cause clinician to explore all available options — conventional and integrative.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    /* Layout + cards */
    .intro-box {
      background-color: #f0f8ff;
      border-left: 5px solid #004080;
      padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
      margin-top: 2rem;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      border-radius: 10px;
      line-height: 1.6;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,.08);
    }
    .grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0,1fr));
      gap: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }
    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }
    .card {
      background: #ffffff;
      border: 1px solid #e6eef7;
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 10px rgba(0,0,0,.06);
    }
    .card h2 { margin: 0 0 .5rem 0; color: #003366; }
    .bullets { margin: .5rem 0 1rem 1.25rem; }
    .bullets li { margin: .25rem 0; }

    /* Highlight sections */
    .highlight-box {
      background: #f9fbff;
      border-left: 6px solid #004080;
      padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
      margin: 1.5rem 0;
      border-radius: 10px;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 10px rgba(0,0,0,.06);
    }
    .provider-callout {
      background: #fff;
      border: 1px dashed #8fb3d9;
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: .75rem 1rem;
      margin-top: .75rem;
    }

    .info-box {
      border-left: 6px solid #004080;
      background: #f0f8ff;
      padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
      margin: 1.5rem 0 2rem 0;
      border-radius: 10px;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 10px rgba(0,0,0,.06);
    }

    .grid-2 {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0,1fr));
      gap: 20px;
      margin-top: .75rem;
      margin-bottom: .75rem;
    }
    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .grid-2 { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }
    .grid-2 h3 { margin: .25rem 0 .25rem 0; color: #003366; }
    .ref { font-size: .95rem; color: #333; }

    .note {
      background: #fff;
      border: 1px solid #e6eef7;
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: .75rem 1rem;
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }

    .btn {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: .5rem .85rem;
      border-radius: 8px;
      border: 1px solid #004080;
      text-decoration: none;
      color: #004080;
      font-weight: 600;
    }
    .btn:hover { background: #004080; color: #fff; }
  </style>
</Layout>

